author: Sutton Coldfield Observer
title: Sutton Coldfield rail passengers given a 'ruff' ride thanks to...
text:
Rail passengers travelling through Sutton Coldfield this afternoon (Friday, September 18) are being held up by an escaped dog on the tracks. 
The dog was found running on tracks near the station at Wylde Green at around 3.30pm today. 
Rail operators London Midland have delayed some trains that pass through the area and made alterations to other services. 
The dog is said to be unhurt.
